HSC Survey Results

Scots Bay Survey # 2 Results from 06/06/2023

Survey Details

8 commercial purse seiners conducted this fishing survey on 06/06/2023 starting at 21:00:00, which was 5.18 hours before high tide.

6 vessels ran two transects each in the Main Survey Box, the Tasha Marie ran four lines in the Eastern Survey Box, and the Brunswick Provider ran four lines in the Northern Survey Box.

There was a plankton tow and replicate conducted and CTD cast by Lady Janice II.

A total of 646 tags were applied during the survey over 3 events from 2023-06-07 to 2023-06-13 from 2 vessels.

Samples were obtained for target strength estimation.

Tides Tables

Tide Schedule for Margaretsville NS, Station #315, Source: www.waterlevels.gc.ca

Acoustic Equipment

Each vessel was equipped with a Simrad ES38-18/200-18C combi (2-in-1) transducer prior to the survey that contains a 38kHz split beam and 200 kHz single beam transducer. Data was logged to the computer hard-drive for post-processing. All participating boats were calibrated on 38kHz before the survey.

Survey Results

Main Results

The results are subject to change as DFO will re-evaluate data editing, area estimation and apply a target strength.

Preliminary biomass prediction for Scots Bay using standardized parallel transects is 113,767mt, and with turnover applied 108,783mt.

Vessel Performance

Speed

Average vessel speed was 8.21. This is above the 8 knot requirement; vessels are urged to slow down to prevent backscatter noise from interfering with the acoustic data.

Distance

No significant distance was cut from the planned lines; vessels covered the planned area well.
